The 2022 edition of the Rashidat Sadiq Basketball Foundation camp rounds off today at the basketball court of the Obafemi Awolowo Stadium, Ibadan. The former D’Tigress forward attracted 100 young girls to the camp, which kicked off on Friday.   TYSON FURY: Joshua, fat purse will bring me out of…     ADAORA ELONU: Basketball ban will ruin many players     AWCON: Kgatlana tips South Africa to dethrone Nigeria   This year’s camp according to the 6’2″ forward has as its theme ‘Strive for Greatness Girls Camp’ According to the Olympian who represented Nigeria at the 2004 Olympic Games, 2006 FIBA World Championship, and the 2006 Commonwealth Games after helping Nigeria triumph at the 2003 and 2005 Afrobasket for Women, the three-day camping for girls, is put together to give the opportunity to young girls to further horn their skill in the dunking game. “I felt it as a duty to give back to young and talented girls to realize that they can make it big in life through basketball and education.”